# apps/web/.env.local.example
#
# Local-only overrides for the Vite dev server (pnpm dev:web).
# Copy to apps/web/.env.local — this file is git-ignored and docker-ignored.
#
# DO NOT create a plain .env file here. Plain .env files inside apps/web/
# are picked up by both local Vite builds AND Docker builds, causing
# localhost:9000 URLs to be baked into the Docker image.
# .env.local is the correct file for local overrides.
#
# ============================================================
# WHEN TO SET VITE_S3_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT:
# ============================================================
#
# Scenario 1: Docker full-stack via nginx (http://localhost:8022)
#   → Leave ALL vars below UNSET.
#   → nginx proxies /cap5/ to MinIO internally.
#   → The frontend uses relative paths automatically.
#
# Scenario 2: Vite dev server (http://localhost:5173) + Docker infra
#   → Uncomment VITE_S3_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:8922
#   → MinIO is mapped to host port 8922.
#
# Scenario 3: Fully local (no Docker, MinIO on :9000)
#   → Uncomment VITE_S3_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9000
#   → Or leave unset — Vite proxy handles /cap5/ → http://localhost:9000
#
# ============================================================

# Uncomment ONE of the following based on your setup:

# Vite dev server + Docker MinIO at :8922
# VITE_S3_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:8922

# Vite dev server + local MinIO at :9000
# VITE_S3_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9000

# Override bucket name (only if you changed S3_BUCKET in .env)
# VITE_S3_BUCKET=cap5
